description: From be- +‎ dumb. Compare Middle English adumbien, from Old English ādumbian (“to become mute or dumb, keep silence, hold one’s peace”).

verbs.description: bedumb (third-person singular simple present bedumbs, present participle bedumbing, simple past and past participle bedumbed)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To make or render dumb, or mute.
